# RNA-BRiQ

This is free software for non-commercial users. If you have any questions,
please contact Peng Xiong via email pengx_a@163.com


Install:

  1, Extract all files

     tar -xvf BRiQ.tar.gz

  2, Change directory to build/ and run compilation

     cd build/
     cmake ../
     make

  3, Edit the .bashrc file and setup the environment variables
 
     vi ~/.bashrc

     add the following sentence

     export BRiQ_DATAPATH=FILEPATH/BRiQ/data
     export PATH=$PATH:FILEPATH/BRiQ/build/bin   

     replace "FILEPATH" with the directory where you extract the files


Run: 

   before running the program, you need to prepare the input file 
   for example: demo/gcaa/input
      pdb gcaa.pdb    #input pdb file
      seq GCGCAAGC    #base sequence
      sec ((....))    #Watson-Crick pairs
      nwc ..(..)..    #Non-Watson-Crick pairs
      fixed 0 1 6 7   #index of fixed nucleotides during structure sampling, start from 0

   If you don't have reference PDB structure, please run BRiQ_init to generate initial model from sequence
   
      BRiQ_init GCGCAAGC init.pdb

   If you want to extract base pairing information from input structure model, please run BRiQ_assignSS

      BRiQ_assign $INPUTPDB $OUTFILE

   RNA structure refinement

      BRiQ_Refinement $INPUT $OUTPDB $RANDOMSEED

   RNA structure prediction
   
      BRiQ_Predict $INPUT $OUTPDB $RANDOMSEED

